claim.claim-text:
8. A method of correlating suspicious events with identified persons, the method comprising:
a) detecting a direct or indirect force that is applied to an object using at least one sensor wherein the force that is applied to the object results in movement of that object from a state of equilibrium;
b) identifying persons in the area associated with a) using at least one proximity detector, wherein the at least one proximity detector collects data of at least one type selected from the group consisting of facial recognition, cell phone MAC address, cell phone beacon and RFID tags;
c) processing data acquired by a) and b) using a microcontroller having an application capable thereof; and
d) communicating the movement of the object detected by the first sensor to the microcontroller of c) using a wired or wireless means of communication.
